# FAAC TODO List (Stack-Ranked by MOS/LoC Ratio)

## Tier 1: High Velocity (Minimal change, maximum quality lift)
- [x] Optimize quantization bias: Implement adaptive rounding (MAGIC_NUMBER) based on tonality and frequency (Addresses "shimmering").
- [x] Refine ATH scaling for VoIP/VSS: Improve speech clarity in low-bitrate 16kHz modes. (Ranked higher due to VoIP MOS bottlenecks).
- [x] Tune transient detection sensitivity in `blockswitch.c`: Reduce pre-echo artifacts.

## Tier 2: Strategic Quality Shifts (Addressing low MOS plateaus)
- [ ] Add bit reservoir control: Solve bit starvation in complex VoIP/VSS frames.
- [ ] Test and optimize TNS (Temporal Noise Shaping): Improve quality for short windows and speech.
- [ ] Implement MDCT-based Psychoacoustic Model (PAM): Reduce CPU by 30-40% and improve masking alignment.

## Tier 3: Standard Alignment & Features
- [ ] Fix scalefactor encoding check (-60 .. 60).
- [ ] Optimize CPE windows grouping: Improve efficiency for stereo signals.
- [ ] Add stereo mode decision hysteresis: Stabilize stereo image in complex soundstages.

- [ ] Add resampler and downmixer.
- [ ] Add HE-AAC support.

## Maintenance & Legacy
- [ ] Test DRM support.
- [ ] Optimize codebook list (section_data).
